# Stage disk-alert secrets — TEMPLATE
#
# Copy this file to ops/alert.local.env on the Pi and fill in real values.
# The real file is GITIGNORED (matched by `*.local.env` + an explicit rule) so
# the bot token never reaches the public repo. NEVER commit a token.
#
#     cp ops/alert.local.env.example ops/alert.local.env
#     chmod 600 ops/alert.local.env          # token is a secret; lock it down
#     # then edit ops/alert.local.env with your real values
#
# disk-alert.sh sources this file automatically (it lives next to the script).
# These are shell `KEY=value` lines, NOT a systemd unit. Do not add `[Service]`.

# --- Telegram Bot API notifier (the default transport) ----------------------
# Why Telegram-curl rather than the `telegram`/`signal` CLIs from ~/.claude:
# those CLIs live on Nick's Mac, not the Pi. The Pi can reach the public
# Telegram Bot API over HTTPS with nothing but curl, so the default notifier is
# a single curl call. Reuse the existing `claude-dreams-telegram` bot token and
# Nick's chat id.
#
# Get a token:  talk to @BotFather (or reuse the claude-dreams-telegram bot).
# Get the chat id:  message the bot, then
#   curl "https://api.telegram.org/bot<TOKEN>/getUpdates" | grep -o '"chat":{"id":[0-9-]*'
STAGE_ALERT_TG_TOKEN=123456789:replace-with-real-bot-token
STAGE_ALERT_TG_CHAT=000000000

# --- Tuning (optional; non-secret, may instead live in the .service) --------
# STAGE_DISK_THRESHOLD=85      # alert at >= this usage percent
# STAGE_DISK_MOUNT=/           # filesystem to watch

# --- Alternative transport (optional) ---------------------------------------
# Set STAGE_ALERT_CMD to REPLACE the Telegram notifier with any command. The
# alert text arrives on stdin, as $1, and in $STAGE_ALERT_MESSAGE. Examples:
#   STAGE_ALERT_CMD='curl -fsS -d "$STAGE_ALERT_MESSAGE" https://ntfy.sh/your-topic'
#   STAGE_ALERT_CMD='signal-cli -u +1555... send -m "$STAGE_ALERT_MESSAGE" +1555...'
